I know what you&#39;re saying... because these debunkers have no scruples... and because they&#39;re cold and ruthless liars like that.... they would simply lift this short statement out of context and smear it everywhere... and say, &quot;See, see even THEY said this!&quot;  I understand your concern.  On the other hand, if it&#39;s not shared with everyone, we may lose the ability to confirm this tech quirk with each other.  With each new confirmation that we get amongst each other, the more we learn and prove this and can improve our other-side communication.  It&#39;s one thing to say that ONLY ONE PERSON hears a certain something, but when we all get together and agree we all hear the same thing, that&#39;s a powerful statement right there.  We all hear help me&#39;s and we hear them disproportinately large amount of times, for scanning AM/FM.... I mean seriously, how often if ever do you hear ANYONE yell &quot;help me&quot; on the radio.... yeah, NEVER is about right... and then to get it multiple times in the same session, and then get it again session after session... that alone is enough irrefutable proof.... to me discussing the possibility that they like to adopt voice communication standard like ten-code is not a big deal, in comparison to how much irrefutable proof we have... it&#39;s just something that might help us to get better rapport with our techs.  But I&#39;ll stop talking about.   

